ur imagination, fueling the flights of invention, storytelling, and empathy that underlie our shared humanity; furthermore, he explains, our tendency to wander back and forth through the timeline of our lives is fundamental to our very sense of ourselves as coherent, continuing personalities. Full of unusual examples and surprising discoveries, The Wandering Mind mounts a vigorous defense of inattention­—even as it never fails to hold the reader’s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAbsent-mindedness. 0aBrain. 0aCognition. 0aThought and thinking. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  abrain, cognition, absent minded, memory, thought, thinking, mind, daydreaming, distraction, psychology, focus, attention, cognitive science, evolutionary biology, imagination, boredom, tedium, invention, storytelling, empathy, emotion, inattention, nonfiction, creativity, subconscious, remembering, literature, history, future, forecasting, planning, dreams, hallucination, delusion, perception, emotional intelligence, body language.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226238753423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226238753/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles